ee months, Sirtech came to Software Etc./Babbages/etc. to sell the game and SE/B/etc. told them to go fuck themselves.  I had to hit 3 stores before I found it.<br><br>Anyways, enough rambling... <p>----------<br>Friar Jaret<br>God bless the <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/bforgottengrailkeepers">Grail Keepers</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ugalendril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galendril</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grimace purple, or Barney purple...<br>Just can't decide!!</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#993300>(1/15/02 12:30:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=160.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizardry 8</span><hr size=1> Looked for it at CompUSA this weekend and didn't see it.  I just assumed it hadn't come out yet.  I am really looking forward to my next CRPG since I recently finished the Baldur's Gate series.<br><br>Does it offer any kind of network play?  It's probably crappy if it does, but it would be neat to try it.<br><br>I might take a pop over at the local software store before I go home tonight to check it out.<br> <p>Galendril Silverdawn<BR><a href=http://www.mithrilheartbrigade.org/><i>Mithril Heart Brigade</i></a><BR><BR>Galen<BR><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/bforgottengrailkeepers><i>Forgotten Grail Keepers</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uwinin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winin</A